HEADWORD: Amelcorn
<hw>Am"el*corn`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Ger.
<ets>amelkorn</ets>: cf. MHG. <ets>amel</ets>, <ets>amer</ets>, spelt,
and L. <ets>amylum</ets> starch, Gr. <?/.]</ety> <def>A variety of wheat
from which starch is produced; -- called also <altname>French
rice</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

